---
description: Stream page data and show in-page skeletons so navigation feels instant
globs: src/routes/**/*.{svelte,ts}
alwaysApply: true
---

# Instant page loading

Pages must switch immediately. Slow data loads **inside** the page shell, not before navigation finishes.

## Pattern

1. In `+page.server.ts`, await only what blocks the route (auth, redirects, `error()`).
2. Return heavier queries as **promises** (do not `await` them in `load`).
3. In `+page.svelte`, resolve with `{#await}` and a skeleton that matches the final layout.
4. Keep the global top progress bar in the root layout for in-flight navigations.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — stream list data
return {
  q,
  recipes: loadPublicRecipes(locals.supabase, q)
};

// ❌ BAD — blocks navigation until the query finishes
const recipes = await loadPublicRecipes(locals.supabase, q);
return { q, recipes };
```

```svelte
{#await data.recipes}
  <RecipeGridSkeleton />
{:then recipes}
  <!-- real content -->
{:catch}
  <p class="alert">{m.error_generic()}</p>
{/await}
```

## Exceptions

- Mutations/`actions` always await as usual.
- Root layout may await session/profile needed for chrome (header avatar, locale sync).

## Checklist for new routes

- [ ] Navigation completes without waiting on list/detail fetches
- [ ] Skeleton mirrors the real layout (grid, hero, form)
- [ ] Auth redirects still happen before any streamed content is returned
